    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-duck-leg-red-wine-bourguignon-with-mash-and-beans/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and halve your <strong>shallots</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> roughly</p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice your<strong> carrot[s]</strong> into rounds</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-duck-leg-red-wine-bourguignon-with-mash-and-beans/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based, hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped chestnut mushrooms </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until beginning to brown</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-duck-leg-red-wine-bourguignon-with-mash-and-beans/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant, then add 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[325ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>,<strong> red wine paste </strong>and <strong>gravy base</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add your <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong>, <strong>carrot rounds </strong>and <strong>shallot halves </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat, top the mixture with your <strong>duck leg[s]</strong> (along with the jelly and fat!) and put in the oven, uncovered, for 30-35 min or until the sauce has reduced the duck is golden and crispy \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy duck leg red wine bourguignon</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-duck-leg-red-wine-bourguignon-with-mash-and-beans/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel your <strong>potatoes</strong> and chop them into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of<strong> boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry, return the potatoes to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of <strong>milk</strong>, then season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and mash until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>mash</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-duck-leg-red-wine-bourguignon-with-mash-and-beans/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes cook, trim then add your <strong>green beans</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil </strong>with a splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the green beans to form a tightly sealed parcel and add to a baking tray</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Make 2 separate parcels!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-duck-leg-red-wine-bourguignon-with-mash-and-beans/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the duck has had around 20 min, put the tray[s] with the <strong>green bean parcel </strong>in the oven for 10-12 min or until the green beans are tender with a slight bite</p><p>Meanwhile, chop your<strong> parsley </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Once the green beans are tender, carefully open the parcel and stir through <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>\u2013 these are your <strong>herby beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-duck-leg-red-wine-bourguignon-with-mash-and-beans/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crispy duck leg red wine bourguignon</strong> with the <strong>mash</strong> and <strong>herby beans</strong> to the side</p><p>Discard the <strong>bay leaf[ves]</strong></p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>remaining chopped parsley </strong>over the top and finish with a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
